I suspect this is not a raw SWT problem. Adding Michael and Boris to increase the visibility.

Are you saying that you can right-click on any other file and the problem does not occur? We (Team) only contribute one action to the context menu of a psf file and it does no special enablement checking. Are you using CVS or another repository provider?

Are you doing this in the resource navigator, the Java package explorer, or the Project Explorer?

Does it happen all the time, or did it happen just once?

I was in the package explorer.  I think this might be a resource issue.  I later was having troubles bringing up menus in just the windows navigator.  They were empty or just had one item. I shutdown a bunch of processes and now I seem to be able to do the operations that were failing.
Sounds like a resource leak to me, which could be anywhere in Callisto.
Where the processes you shut down related to Eclipse or could you have had some other application running that was leaking OS handles?
It would also be interesting to know how long you had worked in Eclipse since you started it, and which components you exercised.
This looks like a leak.  When the operating system runs out of resources, different operating system calls can fail.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 22456 ***
